P1.28 Container Health Check Implementation Notes:

Implementation completed: 2026-03-29

Changes:
- internal/providers/aws.go: Added container-level health check to task definition
  - New deployInput.HealthCheckGracePeriod parameter (default: 60s)
  - Container HEALTHCHECK using CMD-SHELL: curl -f http://localhost:PORT/PATH || exit 1
  - Health check config: interval=30s, timeout=5s, retries=3, startPeriod=grace_period

- internal/providers/aws_test.go: Added TestDeployInput_HealthCheckGracePeriod test

Key decisions:
- Uses curl (standard in most container images) for health check command
- Same health_check_path as ALB for consistency
- Default grace period 60s allows slow-starting apps to initialize
- 3 retries before marking unhealthy to avoid flapping

How it works:
1. Container health check runs inside ECS task (not ALB)
2. ECS monitors container health status independently
3. If container marked unhealthy, ECS stops and replaces the task
4. Works in conjunction with ALB health checks for defense in depth
